              <description><![CDATA[<div id="wikipage">
<div id="wikipage-inner">
<p>This workshop template is based around a number of short    introductions,  activities and reflections exploring the theme: <em>Using    Technologies  in Teaching</em>.  We call it Learning Design 'Lite'   because although it uses the OULDI  methodology the theory of Learning   Design is not explicitly discussed.<strong> </strong><strong><a href="http://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/4876">Please feel free to  use  and adapt this template and tell us how you find it</a></strong></p>
<table style="width: 100%;" border="0">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><img id="pbImage76858" src="http://jiscdesignstudio.pbworks.com/f/1290706991/Readtableshot2.png" alt="" width="246" height="220" /><br /></td>
<td>
<p>The aims of the workshop are:</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<ol>
<li>To give participants an overview of new technologies and how they    can be used</li>
<li>To give participants the chance to critically review the affordances    of technologies and their use in different contexts</li>
<li>To enable them to reflect on the relevance and application to their    own practice</li>
<li>Exposure to a range of Learning Design tools and approaches</li>
</ol>&nbsp;
<p>This workshop was first developed by the OULDI team for the&nbsp;  Design-Practice project (<a href="http://www.design-practice.org/">www.design-practice.org</a>)</p>
<br /></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
