              <title>Template: Learning Design &#39;Lite&#39; Workshop</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/4876</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/4876</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<div id="user-entry">
<p>This workshop is based around a number of short  introductions, activities and reflections exploring the theme: <em>Using  Technologies in Teaching</em>.</p>
<p>The aims of the workshop are:</p>
<ol>
<li>To give participants an overview of new technologies and how they  can be used</li>
<li>To give participants the chance to critically review the affordances  of technologies and their use in different contexts</li>
<li>To enable them to reflect on the relevance and application to their  own practice</li>
<li>Exposure to a range of Learning Design tools and approaches</li>
</ol>
<p>This workshop was first developed for the&nbsp; Design-Practice project (<a href="http://www.design-practice.org/">www.design-practice.org</a>)</p>
